-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/HTMLCollection\"><code>HTMLCollection</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/MutationObserver\"><code>MutationObserver</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NamedNodeMap\"><code>NamedNodeMap</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Node\"><code>Node</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NodeIterator\"><code>NodeIterator</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NodeList\"><code>NodeList</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/ProcessingInstruction\"><code>ProcessingInstruction</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Range\"><code>Range</code></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/StaticRange\"><code>StaticRange</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Text\"><code>Text</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextDecoder\"><code>TextDecoder</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TextEncoder\"><code>TextEncoder</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TimeRanges\"><code>TimeRanges</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/TreeWalker\"><code>TreeWalker</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li><li><a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/XMLDocument\"><code>XMLDocument</code> <small>(en-US)</small></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p></p><p></p>\n\n<p>Ein <strong><code>USVString</code></strong> entspricht der Menge aller möglichen Folgen von Unicode-Skalarwerten. <code>USVString</code> konvertiert zu <code><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\">String</a></code>, wenn es in JavaScript zurückgegeben wird; Es wird allgemein nur für APIs verwendet, die Text verarbeiten und einen String mit Unicode-Skalarwerten benötigen. <code>USVString</code> ist gleich zu <code><a href=\"/de/docs/conflicting/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\">DOMString</a></code>, mit der Ausnahme, dass USVString ungepaarte Ersatzcodepoints nicht erlaubt. Ungepaarte Ersatzcodepoints in einem USVString werden vom Browser zum Unicode 'Ersatzzeichen' <code>U+FFFD</code> konvertiert.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"specification","title":"Spezifikationen","isH3":false,"content":"<table class=\"standard-table\">\n <tbody>\n  <tr>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Spezifikation</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Status</th>\n   <th scope=\"col\">Kommentar</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n   <td><a href=\"https://heycam.github.io/webidl/#idl-USVString\" hreflang=\"en\" lang=\"en\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Web IDL<br><small lang=\"de\">Die Definition von 'USVString' in dieser Spezifikation.</small></a></td>\n   <td><span class=\"spec-cr\">Anwärter Empfehlung</span></td>\n   <td>Initiale Definition.</td>\n  </tr>\n </tbody>\n</table>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"siehe_auch","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><code><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\">String</a></code></li>\n <li><code><a href=\"/de/docs/conflicting/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\">DOMString</a></code></li>\n <li><code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">CSSOMString (en-US)</a></code></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Archive/Add-ons/Code_snippets/StringView\" class=\"page-not-created\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\"><code>StringView</code> - eine C-like Repräsentation von Strings basierend auf Arrays</a></li>\n <li><code><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/btoa\" class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">Binary strings (en-US)</a></code></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Spezifikationen","id":"specification"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"siehe_auch"}],"summary":"Ein USVString entspricht der Menge aller möglichen Folgen von Unicode-Skalarwerten. USVString konvertiert zu String, wenn es in JavaScript zurückgegeben wird; Es wird allgemein nur für APIs verwendet, die Text verarbeiten und einen String mit Unicode-Skalarwerten benötigen. USVString ist gleich zu DOMString, mit der Ausnahme, dass USVString ungepaarte Ersatzcodepoints nicht erlaubt. Ungepaarte Ersatzcodepoints in einem USVString werden vom Browser zum Unicode 'Ersatzzeichen' U+FFFD konvertiert.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"USVString","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"USVString","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"USVString","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/conflicting/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/string_9094f63a1f7efd350dd69d6a8ae174fb","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/conflicting/web/javascript/reference/global_objects/string_9094f63a1f7efd350dd69d6a8ae174fb/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/de/docs/conflicting/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects","title":"uneval()"},{"uri":"/de/docs/conflicting/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String_9094f63a1f7efd350dd69d6a8ae174fb","title":"USVString"}],"pageTitle":"USVString | MDN","noIndexing":true}}